For the impatient:
  # make install

The default prefix (/usr/local) can be overridden on the command line:
  # make PREFIX=/usr install

The default location for config files ($PREFIX/etc/wallpaper) can be
overridden on the command line:
  # make SYSCONFDIR=/etc install

The package can be installed to a staging directory for packaging:
  $ make DESTDIR=$PWD/pkg PREFIX=/usr SYSCONFDIR=/etc install

Deps:
gtkdialog <http://code.google.com/p/gtkdialog/>
